    				<h1 class="head">About the workshop</h1>
    				
    				<p>
    					The 
    					<a href="http://www.icjia.org">
    						Illinois Criminal Justice Information Authority
    					</a>
    					is happy to announce its 2013
    					event for Illinois Law Enforcement Executives. ICJIA has once again partnered with 
    					<a href="http://www.alexanderweissconsulting.com/">
    						Alexander Weiss Consulting, LLC
    					</a>
    					to provide an in-residence, information-rich &
    					demanding program designed to give executives an opportunity to immerse themselves
    					into an environment with likeminded executives concerned with big picture issues
    					in policing, management, leadership and society.
    				</p>
    				
    				<p>
    					The Police Executive Leadership Training Workshop is a 40 hour course that will
    					focus on the executive, business and policing skills required to lead law
    					enforcement agencies through our constantly changing economic and social
    					environment. The Workshop will provide attendees with a sophisticated, dynamic and
    					interactive experience. This year's topics aim to facilitate thought and
    					discussion on the following leadership issues:
    					<ul class="icons-ul">
    						<li>
    							<i class="icon-li icon-ok">
    							</i>
    							The Future of Policing
    						</li>
    						<li>
    							<i class="icon-li icon-ok">
    							</i>
    							Transformational Leadership
    						</li>
    						<li>
    							<i class="icon-li icon-ok">
    							</i>
    							Accountability
    						</li>
    						<li>
    							<i class="icon-li icon-ok">
    							</i>
    							Data-driven Policing
    						</li>
    						<li>
    							<i class="icon-li icon-ok">
    							</i>
    							Strategic Planning
    						</li>
    						<li>
    							<i class="icon-li icon-ok">
    							</i>
    							Collaboration
    						</li>
    					</ul>
    				</p>
