						<h6>Pat Connolly</h6>
						<div class="member-title">Chief, Urbana Police</div>
						<div class="member-agency">&nbsp;</div>
						<div class="member-bio">
						<span class="expander">
							<img src="img/headshots/connolly.png" alt="Pat Connolly"/>
							<p></p>Urbana Police Chief Patrick Connolly began his law enforcement career in 1977 
							when, for six years, he was assigned as a Special Agent with the Air 
							Force Office of Special Investigations.  In 1984 he left active duty military service to develop Champaign County's 
							first Intensive Probation Supervision program.  Four years later, he began his career with the Urbana Police Department, 
							and since that time has touched every division within the department including patrol, criminal investigations, 
							two specialized narcotics units, two first line supervisory positions, two commander level positions, the METRO/SWAT 
							Commander, the Assistant Chief of Police and most recently, Urbana's Chief of Police. </p> 

<p>Chief Connolly graduated from PTI in 1988 and is also a graduate of Eastern Illinois University.  Additional Law Enforcement Academies include, Northwestern's Staff and Command School (160th Session) and the FBI National Academy (230th Session).    In 2003 he retired from the United States Air Force with over twenty-four years of combined service.
</p>

<p>
Pat has lectured at various law enforcement communities throughout the US and abroad 
including the Ukraine as well as to the Chinese Delegation of the 2008 Olympic Committee.  
He is also the primary instructor for the Illinois Law Enforcement Alarm System (ILEAS) Mobile Field Force teams.</p> 

								
								
								
							
						</span>
