<p>Mr. Furcon is a frequent speaker at professional meetings, business events and webcasts.  He has authored a number of articles, papers, reports, and psychological assessment tools, including "Workforce Engagement and Retention in the United States," "Building 21st Century Senior Leaders," "Motivational Antecedents of the Work Performance of Scientists and Engineers," "Municipal Police and State Highway Patrol Officer Selection," and the "Job Requirements Audit and he has been recognized in "Who's Who in America" and "Who's Who in the World."
</p>
<p>Mr. Furcon's professional memberships include: The Chicago Council on Global Affairs, Human Resources Management Association of Chicago, Illinois Association of Chiefs of Police, International Association of Chiefs of Police, Society of Industrial and Organizational Psychology, and The World Future Society.  Mr. Furcon has a Masters of Business Administration in Organization Behavior at the University of Chicago Booth School of Business and the Master of Arts in Psychology at DePaul University.
