				<div class="span6">
					<div class="board-member">
						
						
						<h6>Brett C. Railey</h6>
						<div class="member-title">Police Chief</div>
						<div class="member-agency">Winter Park, Florida</div>
						<div class="member-bio">
						<span class="expander">
							<img src="img/headshots/railey.png" alt="Brett C. Railey"/>
							<p>Chief  Brett Railey&rsquo;s law enforcement career began in 1977 as a dispatcher for the  Florida Highway Patrol and as a campus police officer at Rollins College.  In 1981, Chief Railey joined the Winter Park,  Florida Police Department as a patrol officer.   In 2009, he was appointed Winter Park Chief of Police.</p>
<p>Chief  Railey has served as SWAT sniper, a Hostage Negotiator and has supervised  Criminal Investigations Detectives, Narcotics Detectives, the Crisis Team,  Special Operations Division, Traffic Enforcement unit, School Resource unit,  Marine Patrol, and the K-9 Division.   Through his career, Chief Railey served as an instructor in Breath Testing,  DUI Enforcement and Standardized Field Sobriety testing.  Chief Railey was selected by the Florida  Prosecuting Attorney&rsquo;s Association to train new prosecutors in the area of  field sobriety testing and currently focuses his instruction on highway safety  and management training.</p>
<p>Chief  Railey is a graduate of the Indiana University Alcohol and Highway Safety,  Supervision and Expert Testimony program and was selected to teach traffic  safety and zero tolerance enforcement to law enforcement officials in the U.S.  Virgin Islands, the Navajo Nation Police and the Brazilian National Police  Force.  He was also requested to introduce  the Data Driven Approaches to Crime and Traffic Safety concept to the Health  Ministers and law enforcement leaders in the country of Mexico. In March of 2012, he presented at the  International Training Workshop for Cadres of Traffic and Transport Ministries  in the State of Kuwait for the Minister of the Interior under a United Nations  initiative to develop a National Traffic and Transport Strategy for Kuwait and  in August of 2012, Chief Railey presented traffic safety concepts to police  officers and executives in Cali, Columbia South America.  In April of 2013, Chief Railey presented at  the Conference on Urban Traffic Safety - Transformational Leadership in Traffic  Safety in Edmonton, Alberta, Canada.</p>
<p>In  addition to training law enforcement agencies across the country, Chief Railey  has presented at the National Institute of Justice Crime Mapping Conference  (Miami, FL), the National Lifesavers Conference (Phoenix, AZ and Orlando, FL),  the Governors Highway Safety Association Conference (Cincinnati, OH), the  Louisiana Police Chiefs Association Conference (Baton Rouge, LA), the Regional  Law Enforcement Liaison Conference (Mobile, AL) and the International  Association of Chiefs of Police Conference (San Diego, CA).</p>
<p>Chief  Railey is Past Chairman of the Highway Safety Committee for the Florida Police  Chief&rsquo;s Association (F.P.C.A.) and is Co-chair of the Statewide Disaster Relief  Committee. In July of 2012, Chief Railey  was elected 3rd Vice President of the FPCA.  Chief Railey is an appointee to Florida  Governor Rick Scott&rsquo;s Pill Mill Strike Force as Co-Chair of the Central Florida  Drug Enforcement Strike Force.  He is a  member of the Governing Board of the Central Florida High Intensity Drug  Trafficking Area (H.I.D.T.A.) and the Governing Board of the Metropolitan  Bureau of Investigation.</p>
<p>Chief  Railey has a B.A. in Applied Behavioral Science from National-Louis University.</p>
